BettyÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s Blends: Live at Great American Music Hall, San Francisco was recorded on December 11, 12, 14, 15 and 16 of 2012. Recorded and mastered Betty Cantor-Jackson, a longtime recording engineer for the Grateful Dead. Almost from the outset, the Dead were meticulous about taping their concerts.
During several periods in their history, Cantor-Jackson did the taping, mixing the soundboard feed directly onto a two-track tape as the music was being performed.
The Chris Robinson Brotherhood is Chris Robinson (lead vocals, guitar), Neal Casal (guitar, vocals), Adam MacDougall (keys, vocals), George Sluppick (drums) and Mark Dutton (bass, vocals). Robinson and co. strike a psychedelic balance between lush jamming and bluesy rocking. The result is a real trip down the rabbit hole complete with some of RobinsonÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s most poetic lyrics and truly impressive musicianship. ItÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s a fascinating, fiery, and formidable introduction to the group and one of the year.
